      "note_no": "55",
      "note": "Lit., \"none of you but will reach it\". According to some of the classical authorities, the pronoun \"you\" relates to the sinners spoken of in the preceding passages, and particularly to those who refuse to believe in resurrection; the majority of the commentators, however, are of the opinion that all human beings, sinners and righteous alike, are comprised within this address in the sense that all \"will come within sight of it\": hence my rendering."
